.TH "sbi_remote_hfence_gvma_vmid" 9 "sbi_remote_hfence_gvma_vmid" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
sbi_remote_hfence_gvma_vmid \- Execute HFENCE.GVMA instructions on given remote harts for a guest physical address range belonging to a specific VMID.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" sbi_remote_hfence_gvma_vmid
.BI "(const unsigned long *hart_mask "  ","
.BI "unsigned long start "  ","
.BI "unsigned long size "  ","
.BI "unsigned long vmid "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hart_mask" 12
A cpu mask containing all the target harts.
.IP "start" 12
Start of the guest physical address
.IP "size" 12
Total size of the guest physical address range.
.IP "vmid" 12
The value of guest ID (VMID).
.SH "RETURN"
0 if success, Error otherwise.
